messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/orders/{id}

All methods acceptable
- false

HEAD
- false

POST
- false

OPTIONS
- false

TRACE
- false

GET
- true

PUT
- false

DELETE
- false

PATCH
- false

Explanation
- The server mounts orderRoutes at the prefix /api/orders in server.js: app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes).
- In routes/orderRoutes.js the route for the controller getOrderById is declared as router.route('/:id').get(protect, getOrderById); which corresponds to the full path /api/orders/:id (written above as /api/orders/{id}).
- Only the GET method is registered for that path in the route file. No handlers for HEAD/POST/OPTIONS/TRACE/PUT/DELETE/PATCH are defined for /:id in the source, so based on the code (not framework runtime behavior) those methods are not acceptable.
- "All methods acceptable" is false because the code explicitly registers only GET for this path.
